title: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
overview: A senator returns to a western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

title: High Noon
overview: A town Marshal, despite the disagreements of his newlywed bride and the townspeople around him, must face a gang of deadly killers alone at high noon when the gang leader, an outlaw he sent up years ago, arrives on the noon train.

title: True Grit
overview: A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

title: Unforgiven
overview: Retired Old West gunslinger William Munny reluctantly takes on one last job, with the help of his old partner Ned Logan and a young man, The "Schofield Kid."

title: Giù la testa
overview: A low-life bandit and an I.R.A. explosives expert rebel against the government and become heroes of the Mexican Revolution.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: Giant
overview: Sprawling epic covering the life of a Texas cattle rancher and his family and associates.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: Hiroshima mon amour
overview: A French actress filming an anti-war film in Hiroshima has an affair with a married Japanese architect as they share their differing perspectives on war.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Gran Torino
overview: Disgruntled Korean War veteran Walt Kowalski sets out to reform his neighbor, Thao Lor, a Hmong teenager who tried to steal Kowalski's prized possession: a 1972 Gran Torino.

title: Nuovo Cinema Paradiso
overview: A filmmaker recalls his childhood when falling in love with the pictures at the cinema of his home village and forms a deep friendship with the cinema's projectionist.

title: Black Hawk Down
overview: 160 elite U.S. soldiers drop into Somalia to capture two top lieutenants of a renegade warlord and find themselves in a desperate battle with a large force of heavily-armed Somalis.

title: Bom Yeoareum Gaeul Gyeoul Geurigo Bom
overview: A boy is raised by a Buddhist monk in an isolated floating temple where the years pass like the seasons.

title: Bronenosets Potemkin
overview: In the midst of the Russian Revolution of 1905, the crew of the battleship Potemkin mutiny against the brutal, tyrannical regime of the vessel's officers. The resulting street demonstration in Odessa brings on a police massacre.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Le passé
overview: An Iranian man deserts his French wife and her two children to return to his homeland. Meanwhile, his wife starts up a new relationship, a reality her husband confronts upon his wife's request for a divorce.
